# Gesture Vocalizer System - Project Summary

## Overview
A smart glove-based system that translates hand gestures into text and speech in real-time, designed to assist deaf and mute individuals.

## Key Features
- Word-level gesture recognition using Arduino and sensors
- Fingerspelling ASL recognition using CNN
- Real-time text and speech output
- Autocorrect feature using Hunspell

## Results
- Accuracy: 93%
- Precision: 95.19%
- Recall: 93.1%
- F1 Score: 94.08%

